node.text:
Here’s the recipe for the keto vanilla birthday cake I made with Ube cream cheese frosting! This was a fun experiment. I was genuinely surprised by how moist and fluffy the cake came out! BTW, definitely also had “real” cake...and milkshakes...and bread pudding too cuz...there’s no holding back on your birthday!!!

Cake ingredients: 

3 c almond flour
1 c coconut flour
4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1.5 c vegan butter, softened
1.5 c monkfruit sugar
8 eggs
1 c almond milk
2 tsp vanilla extract

Ube cream cheese frosting ingredients:

1 c monkfruit powdered sugar
16 oz vegan cream cheese, softened
1/2 c softened vegan butter
1/2 tsp of ube extract

Method:

1. Mix all cake ingredients together
2. Bake for 45 min - 1 hr depending on your oven, until firm on top, at 350 F
3. Once firm, remove from oven, let cool, then slice into 2 or 3 layers
4. For frosting, whip all ingredients together, then chill in fridge
5. Once both the cake and frosting are cool, add frosting between each layer of cake, and then on the outside
6. Slice and enjoy!

Makes 16 servings!

Recipe adapted from @thebigmansworld keto birthday cake.

I wanted to see once and for all what simple 2-3 ingredient healthy cookie recipe would taste the best! So, I put 5 recipes against each other!

1.5 banana + 1/2 c coconut flour

1 banana + 1/2 c rolled oats

1.5 banana + 1/2 c pea protein

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut

1 banana + 1/2 c dessicated coconut + 1/2 c peanut powder

Watch the video to find which recipe failed and which recipe won! I’m always looking for an easy staple healthy cookie recipe...which do you wanna try?

node.text:
I love dancing! It is my favorite form of cardio because it never feels like cardio, you know what I mean?! I'm sad that I can't take dance classes or fitness classes right now, but it's all good because we need to do our part to flatten the curve! And that means social distancing!
.
Anyway, my friend @thefitnessmarshall tagged me in the Your Turn Dance Challenge and I was like nooooo SO MUCH CHOREO TO LEARN but once I got started it wasn't that bad. Thank you Caleb for the lil push :) I had a lot of fun getting my groove on, so if you guys wanna learn it too, just follow my tutorial! I tacked on the last 4 counts and YES IT INCLUDES A HAIR WHIP YOU ARE VERY WELCOME.
.
Here's how this all got started BTW!
.
1️⃣Started by @daniellenatoni - this challenge is designed to see how much choreography we can build by each person adding 4 counts at a time!
2️⃣Danielle then threw it to @officialtaniabaron who did her 4 counts who then threw it to @shaunt who threw it to @drlaurenfitz who thew it to @thefitnessmarshall who has now thrown it to me!
3️⃣I added on my own 4 counts inspired by my heels classes and NOW I CHALLENGE MY LIL SISTER @jackelynho to add the next 4 counts!
4️⃣Who will be next and how long will this keep going?!?😍🙌🏼🤷🏼‍♀️
#yourturndancechallenge #dance #dancechallenge #socialdistancing

Interesting how there’s so much prejudice when it comes to weight. And I’m not even talking about hundreds of pounds. Just twenty.

These are real comments I received. It’s pretty striking to see how members of different communities view the same exact thing. My body. 

[Side note: I’m going to use the terms “fat” and “skinny” going forward in this post to define me 20 lbs heavier versus now for simplicity of writing.]

FAT IN A BIKINI
1️⃣“You’re so inspirational and so brave!”
2️⃣ “Why don’t you have abs??”

SKINNY IN A BIKINI
1️⃣“I liked you better before…”
2️⃣ “Too thin.”

FAT WHILE TEACHING WORKOUTS
1️⃣“I like seeing a normal body do these workouts.”
2️⃣ “If you cared about your career, you’d lose weight.”

SKINNY WHILE TEACHING WORKOUTS
1️⃣“You have an eating disorder.”
2️⃣ “She doesn’t even workout. She’s just skinny.”

And to sum it all up…

BEFORE 90 DAY JOURNEY:
“You’re a bad role model for all women!!! Hypocrite! UNFOLLOW.”

AFTER 90 DAY JOURNEY:
“How did you do it?”

I’m not going up call out the specific communities (and genders) making these remarks about my body and my intentions, but it was very much coming from members of groups with views so strong, it made them narrow minded. And you know what? That is so dangerous. Because it cuts you off from solution oriented thinking and in general, having empathy for other people’s individual backgrounds and journeys. It breeds ignorance too.

The point is: focus on yourself and your journey. Look at what other people did for inspiration and for guidance, but don’t compare! And finally, it goes without saying, but saying it anyway, think about what you write.

We weren’t talking about mental health several years ago the way we are doing now, and I’m just so grateful I’m still here. So many of my fellow creators have burned out and left due to a myriad of personal reasons, but they all shared the burden of battling hateful comments and letting that affect their self worth. The truth is, my skin and heart have both thickened over the years in order to still be here. It’s not easy, but it’s ok. I’m ok.

Anyway, thank you for still being here with me. Your support helps me believe in myself everyday.

♥️Cassey

Mixing food and feet cuz why not 💁🏻‍♀️

I still remember the first time you guys asked me to make socks years ago and I was so confused about yarns, knitting, and basically feet in general! 😵‍💫 I remember my initial samples coming back so thin, so big and honestly, really ugly. It was disastrous.

Never went to fashion school but lots of trial and error + resilience = the best teacher.

Today, I bring you my cutest @popflex_active sock set ever!!! Not only are they super soft, supportive but not too tight, breathable and not too thick, they’re all inspired by FOOD, and they have a silicone strip inside to keep your sock from sliding off inside your shoe!

I made 7 in a pack so you have one for everyday of the week without having to do your laundry to find your fave pair of socks! V IMPORTANT AMIRITE!?

Here are the designs:

🫐Acai bowl - umm duh, I love açaí bowls forever and ever!!!

🌶Hot sauce - a tribute to my love for everything spicy!

🥑Avocado toast - my fave breakfast food! (But make it gluten free and throw on a ton of Everything but the Elote Seasoning from TJ’s)

🍦Ice cream - I mean, do I even need to explain.

🥞Pancakes - make it 2 ingredient Blogilates banana pancakes.

🍳 Eggs - perfect protein and fat food. 

☕️Coffee - soooooo coffee. Those of you who know me know that I can’t eat chocolate or coffee because it tastes super bitter to me. I’m a supertaster. My tastebuds are overactive basically. So I kinda wish I didn’t do coffee and instead did matcha because that’s my morning drink of choice but then I already had the green from avocado toast so here we are.  I felt coffee was a generally relatable food. If I remake these I might take out the coffee and replace with something else. So limited edition run I guess! 😅

Which one is your favorite!?

♥️Cassey

Since my “lack of desire for children” post, I’ve talked to sooooooo many friends who’ve opened up to me about the subject - from every possible angle! It’s been so nice to have one on one girl dates and talk about this stuff because it’s not really an “accepted” topic of discussion.

I want to share some perspectives that I found super interesting:

1️⃣ “It was a powerful feeling and I want to do it again.” - A mother of 2 who ENJOYED the actual birthing process! This is the part I’m REALLY REALLY REALLY scared of because I have very low pain tolerance for non-workout things but when she said she felt like she accomplished something POWERFUL and had more respect for her body afterwards, the challenge-loving part of me perked up.

2️⃣ “I looked at my watch and was like, ok I guess it’s time.” A newly pregnant mom who is extremely career oriented, ambitious and whose husband wanted kids more than she did. She was super open about having a lack of desire like me and said it was more of a logical decision not an emotional one when it came to getting pregnant. She played out her life in front of her and decided it was simply the right time to begin to process. (She’s a doctor.) Side note: she now loves being pregnant!
 
3️⃣ “Just visit a fertility clinic, get tested and empower yourself with information.” A workaholic friend who is struggling with low egg count because of either stress or age and wants at least a chance to have kids. I never really thought about how much stress can affect your body when it comes to egg production, so this is something I’m going to have to watch out for. I don’t FEEL stressed but I know I don’t sleep enough and I work, A LOT.

4️⃣ “I don’t want to love my husband second.” An extremely successful businesswoman who adamantly doesn’t want kids, doesn’t want to sacrifice her lifestyle, or her relationship with her husband. She wants to love him first, and he wants to love her first too. I like that she very much knows what she wants. I don’t feel like she does towards kids, so it’s not that I am against them, it’s just that I don’t have a strong feeling FOR them. I just feel neutral, if that makes sense.

How do you feel?

♥️Cassey

“But what does it do?” You know. Fair question.

Some people follow my page to lose weight, others to gain strength, some to to find a consistent routine they can stick to OR MAYBE YOU’RE JUST CREEPIN - but there are many different ways to do the same move for different results.

To lose who want to lose weight - DO this fast and you’ll not only tone your thighs, but also this move acts as cardio to aid fat loss.

To those who want to gain strength - do this slow and controlled, and hold your leg up when you lift to get stronger and gain more muscle in your thighs and glutes. Add ankle weights if you want even more!

If you are looking for a consistent routine - try this move and if you like it, add it daily as a mini challenge for a week! But if you’re looking for a true regimen, it’s best to choose a program that matches your goals on my app @bodybyblogilates (free to download) and commit to it. (Beginners Calendar, 21 Day Tone, 7 Day Ab Challenge, Hot Girl Summer Sculpt etc).

And if you’re just creepin, thanks for the views.

😉

OKAY BUT SERIOUSLY GO TRY THIS MOVE! IT’S KILLER!

♥️Cassey

STORYTIME: Did you know that before there was Blogilates there was “oGorgeous”?

Okay so it was junior year of college, I was sitting in Intro to Marketing and I was trying to come up with a name for my future yoga bag company. Backstory - I was teaching Pilates as my side hustle and encountered a problem: there weren’t any cute bags that could hold my mat, CDs, keys, water bottle, and gym towel. So I decided to solve the problem by making one myself!

In class we were discussing Apple and how clever it was for them to put a little lowercase “i” in front of all of their products: iPhone, iPad etc. So I thought…BRILLIANT! I am going to choose another letter and put that in front of a word too! I chose little “o” because it was round and even. Then “gorgeous” because I wanted my brand to be identified with pretty things. And there it was. In 2008, in Intro to Marketing at Whittier College, the name “oGorgeous” was born and that’s what I called my bags, and eventually…

It morphed into the official incorporated name of my entire company 😅

To be COMPLETELY honest, I SO WISH the company name was NOT THAT. I wish it was literally anything without a little letter in front because knowing that I choose little “o” due to being over-inspired by little “i”, and the fact that no other little letter ever captured the global brand awareness that Apple has been able to accomplish makes me feel like I’m the only one who’s still wearing skinny jeans while the world has moved on to baggy. 😫

My YouTube channel Blogilates came in 2009 and then POPFLEX in 2016. What makes me cringe the most is that whenever I have to spell out “oGorgeous” to people, they always add an apostrophe so it’s capital O’Gorgeous and then they proceed to ask me about our company’s Irish roots 🍀

ANYWAY.

In the sprit of bags, I’m excited to share with you 2 new @popflex_active bag colors inspired by my ♥️ of everything tropical! I brought my Belladonna in Bora Blue on my honeymoon to actual Bora Bora! 🌴 She was the perfect carryon and Mavourneen Mini went with me everywhere because she holds my giant bottle exactly. All styles also come in Sand too! Which color speaks to you more?

♥️Cassey

MY. MIND. IS. BLOWN. 🤯

I just made vegan “yogurt” in 2 min and the texture is just like the real thing! I AM NOT KIDDING. To all my lactose intolerant people, you NEED this in your life! This recipe would be great as a post workout refuel since its made with @housefoodsamerica tofu and packs in a ton of protein. 

Tofu is a perfect plant based 🌱 alternative for anyone looking for some extra protein! But you don’t have to be vegan to love it. I’m not and I eat tofu all the time.

Vanilla “Yogurt” Ingredients:

▫️16 oz block of extra firm tofu from @housefoodsamerica #ad
▫️Juice of 3 limes
▫️2-4 TBS monkfruit sugar (I like 4 bc I like sweeter) or any sweetener of your choice
▫️2 TBS vanilla extract

Method:

1️⃣ Blend all together until smooth
2️⃣ Top with fruit and/or granola to create a parfait

I would also like to add that this tofu yogurt is @samlivits approved!

♥️Cassey

node.text:
Apparently it’s National Sister’s Day but everyday is sister’s day for me!

I know it’s typical for a younger sister to look up to to her bigger sister but I have to tell you, I’ve always been impressed by @jackelynho. She’s this intricate mix of hard work but chill vibes, ambition but contentment; she’s creatively advantageous but also incredibly generous.

I’ve always admired how @jackelynho is fearless in her pursuit of what she wants. In fact…

When it came to living with a boy for the first time, she trailblazed that for me. I had been secretly living with @samlivits…pretending he was my roommate. We even had a fake bedroom set up whenever my parents would visit! Sorry mom, I know you’re reading this 😬

When it came to school, she unapologetically went hard into a non-traditional field for children of Asian immigrants. She majored in journalism and got to study abroad - something I’ll always regret not doing because my parents had enforced a strict timeline on my academic studies towards becoming a doctor. 

And when it comes to pushing me out of my comfort zone, she’s not afraid to drag me into a new world because she knows it’s good for me. Prime example. Running. She made do my first half marathon. I hated it. Made me run some other race. Still hated it. Then the pandemic hit. Forced me to run with her. I cried and said no. Well guess what? Over a year and a half later, I run every single morning. It somehow turned from torture to treasure. And all because she pushed me to find that for myself.

Above on the left, that’s a picture from 2015 of me and @jackelynho playing dress up, manifesting her wedding day! On the right, her actual wedding day May 29, 2021.

I’m so grateful to have @jackelynho as my little sister and forever inspiration. I’m so glad my mom kept trying for a second child after having so much trouble conceiving, even dealing with a miscarriage. My life would have been so different without Jackelyn. It really is another thing to consider if/when @samlivits and I have kids because sisterhood is so special and I continue to cherish every moment of it.

Do you have a sister?

♥️Cassey

The fitness industry is a weird place. Trainer bodies are treated like billboards and the ones with the best selling programs or the most followers are the ones with the most “desirable” bodies.

It’s the truth. I know this because I’ve lived it.

No matter how much I try to explain that how you look is hugely affected by your genetics, people with great butts can sell booty programs and then I get asked if my workouts even work because of how flat mine is 🙄 Same thing with abs. I have an extremely strong core from years of Pilates but still get asked why I don’t have abs.

On the contrary, whenever I post an arm workout like this one, it always gets a bunch of views because simply put - my arms look lean and cut.

My “billboard” for arms seems trustworthy. Whereas my “billboard” for glutes doesn’t create a strong visual promise for the viewer. It’s a what-you-see-is-what-you-get mentality with fitness, but the truth is, THE BODY DOESN’T WORK LIKE THAT. 

If we’re talking just physical, fat loss and muscle growth happens at different rates in different parts of your body. Plus, it’s all connected! For example…want big boobs and a tiny waist? Many bikini competitors have to get breast implants because they lose so much fat when they get super lean. Even I considered it after I competed for the first time…

Anyway, wanted to share that to tell you this: don’t get sold by a billboard. Go deeper. Look behind the visual and find the joy. The real reason why you’re gonna wake up every morning, even when you’re older, itching to get outta bed and get sweaty. It’s gonna be because you love how it feels. Not because you wanna be skinny. Yeah, maybe that works for a little while, but not forever. Vapid goals die quick.

Oh! And just dropped some new Pilates workouts in @fitonapp! #ad You can’t find these on YouTube or in my app, it’s exclusive, so def go download the app because it’s free. Legit can’t believe it still is with all the cinematic quality workout videos in there! You can even do dance workouts, yoga, HIIT, stretching - it’s a seriously good group of instructors but instead of driving to the gym you can just do everything at home!

♥️Cassey

12 years ago, I visited NYC for the first time in my life. Here’s what was going on:

It was 2009. I had just graduated with a Biology degree that I wanted nothing to do with, my parents absolutely disapproved of me following my passion (design), the recession made it hard to get hired anywhere, and I felt…so lost…so out of place…so defeated. Career wise.

Relationship wise, I had been with my new boyfriend @samlivits for a year at this point and we were madly in love. We didn’t have enough money to get a hotel, so we asked one of Sam’s friends if we could crash with him in his tiny East Village basement. We never took a single yellow cab (walking and subway only!), we mostly ate at food trucks and once in a while treated ourselves to a hole in the wall restaurant, and you know what? It was perfect. We loved the city so much but didn’t know how or when we could visit again.

Well, life has it’s funny ways if you keep pushing, keep believing, and keep being resilient in the face of failure.

Since 2009, Sam and I have flown to New York more than any other city in the world! And the best part? It’s for work…doing things I’m passionate about. The very things my parents told me I need to stop doing because I was “wasting my time”. From teaching Pilates in Times Square to ringing the bell at NASDAQ to appearing on multiple national live TV shows, I seriously cannot believe how far baby Sam and Cassey have come.

And you wanna know something funny? Today after I did my segment on @livekellyandryan teaching Pilates to @mariamenounos and @ryanseacrest using @popflex_active yoga mats and POPFLEX booty bands (omg!!!) we decided to celebrate by walking all the way from Times Square to Washington Park (12,000 steps for fun) and grabbing lunch at some hole in the wall. Then when it started raining a bit, I told Sam I wanted to take a cab back Uptown but he was adamant about taking the Subway. He thinks it’s “fun.” 🤔

Hey. Some things change and some things don’t.

I’m just so happy that today, in 2021, the confidence I have in myself, my business, and my relationship is stronger than ever. I am so grateful for this journey.

♥️Cassey

IT WORKS.

🤯

I am always learning something new from you guys 😅 

Anyway! Just dropped this new Marine Marble set on @popflex_active! The Lavender version sold out so quick last time that I wanted to bring this set back in an additional option for you! New color, same ButterSoft.

And seriously…thank you for your enthusiasm. Your love for POPFLEX gives me more confidence as a designer. I never went to school for fashion and sometimes get major imposter syndrome. Every time I see you wear the clothes and how it hugs your body just right, my heart fills with a bit more fullness. I’ll never stop learning in this school of life and I hope to keep making you cool things til I can’t draw anymore.
